PERMUTATION IN STRING  (Check Inclusion)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Given two strings s1 and s2, return true if s2 contains a permutation of s1.
Return false otherwise.

A permutation means same characters with same frequency,
but order can be different.


EXAMPLE 1
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input:  s1 = "ab", s2 = "eidbaooo"
Output: true
Explanation: substring "ba" is a permutation of "ab"


EXAMPLE 2
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input:  s1 = "ab", s2 = "eidboaoo"
Output: false


CONSTRAINTS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1 <= s1.length, s2.length <= 10^4
Only lowercase English letters


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BRUTE FORCE (YOUR CODE — KEEPING CONTENT, CLEAN FORMAT)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Time Complexity : O(26 * n * k)
Space Complexity: O(1)

class Solution {
public:
    bool checkInclusion(string s1, string s2)
    {
        vector<int> temp(26,0);
        int k = s1.size();

        for(int i = 0; i < k; i++)
            temp[s1[i]-'a']++;

        for(int i = 0; i < s2.length(); i++)
        {
            int wnidx = 0;
            int idx = i;
            vector<int> temp1(26,0);

            while(wnidx < k && idx < s2.length())
            {
                temp1[s2[idx]-'a']++;
                wnidx++;
                idx++;
            }

            if(temp == temp1)
                return true;
        }

        return false;
    }
};


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
OPTIMAL — SLIDING WINDOW (INTERVIEW EXPECTED)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

IDEA:
• Count frequency of s1
• Maintain window of size k in s2
• Add right char, remove left char
• Compare frequency arrays

Time Complexity : O(26 * n) ≈ O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

class Solution {
public:
    bool checkInclusion(string s1, string s2)
    {
        if(s1.size() > s2.size()) return false;

        vector<int> need(26,0), window(26,0);

        for(char c : s1)
            need[c-'a']++;

        int k = s1.size();

        for(int i = 0; i < s2.size(); i++)
        {
            window[s2[i]-'a']++;

            if(i >= k)
                window[s2[i-k]-'a']--;

            if(window == need)
                return true;
        }

        return false;
    }
};
